<subSubSection pageId="5" pageNumber="6" type="description">
<paragraph blockId="5.[151,1437,290,956]" pageId="5" pageNumber="6">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,303,290,316]" pageId="5" pageNumber="6">Description.</emphasis>
Body length: ɗ, 
<quantity box="[512,597,290,316]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="7.4" pageId="5" pageNumber="6" unit="mm" value="7.4">7.4mm</quantity>
; Ψ, 
<number box="[647,684,290,316]" pageId="5" pageNumber="6" value="9.7">9.7</number>
–10.0mm. Head and thorax generally black, vertex with brown basally laterally, gena and anteclypeus generally brown, anteclypeus with pair of black spots apically. Pronotum brown laterally. Scutellum with some short tufts of setae laterally.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="5.[151,1437,290,956]" pageId="5" pageNumber="6">
Male pygofer with distal margin broadly rounded in lateral view (
<figureCitation box="[1019,1093,410,436]" captionStart="FIGURE 3" captionStartId="16.[151,255,1541,1565]" captionTargetBox="[202,1390,252,1497]" captionTargetId="figure@16.[163,1439,194,1517]" captionTargetPageId="16" captionText="FIGURE 3. Cyrta hornei, E-F are after Zhang &amp; Wei (2002). A, male genital capsule, lateral view; B, male genital capsule, dorsal view; C, valve and subgenital plates, ventral view; D, connective and style, dorsal view; E, aedeagus, ventral view; F, style, connective and aedeagus, lateral view." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/182579/files/figure.png" pageId="5" pageNumber="6">
Fig. 
<number box="[1079,1093,410,436]" pageId="5" pageNumber="6" value="3.0">3</number>
</figureCitation>
A); subgenital plate slightly extending beyond apex of pygofer side, apex acute in ventral view (
<figureCitation box="[939,1008,450,476]" captionStart="FIGURE 3" captionStartId="16.[151,255,1541,1565]" captionTargetBox="[202,1390,252,1497]" captionTargetId="figure@16.[163,1439,194,1517]" captionTargetPageId="16" captionText="FIGURE 3. Cyrta hornei, E-F are after Zhang &amp; Wei (2002). A, male genital capsule, lateral view; B, male genital capsule, dorsal view; C, valve and subgenital plates, ventral view; D, connective and style, dorsal view; E, aedeagus, ventral view; F, style, connective and aedeagus, lateral view." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/182579/files/figure.png" pageId="5" pageNumber="6">
Fig. 
<number box="[993,1008,450,476]" pageId="5" pageNumber="6" value="3.0">3</number>
</figureCitation>
C). Aedeagal shaft bifurcate apically in dorsal view (
<figureCitation box="[333,401,490,516]" captionStart="FIGURE 3" captionStartId="16.[151,255,1541,1565]" captionTargetBox="[202,1390,252,1497]" captionTargetId="figure@16.[163,1439,194,1517]" captionTargetPageId="16" captionText="FIGURE 3. Cyrta hornei, E-F are after Zhang &amp; Wei (2002). A, male genital capsule, lateral view; B, male genital capsule, dorsal view; C, valve and subgenital plates, ventral view; D, connective and style, dorsal view; E, aedeagus, ventral view; F, style, connective and aedeagus, lateral view." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/182579/files/figure.png" pageId="5" pageNumber="6">
Fig. 
<number box="[387,401,490,516]" pageId="5" pageNumber="6" value="3.0">3</number>
</figureCitation>
E). Xth segment elongate (
<figureCitation box="[716,786,490,516]" captionStart="FIGURE 3" captionStartId="16.[151,255,1541,1565]" captionTargetBox="[202,1390,252,1497]" captionTargetId="figure@16.[163,1439,194,1517]" captionTargetPageId="16" captionText="FIGURE 3. Cyrta hornei, E-F are after Zhang &amp; Wei (2002). A, male genital capsule, lateral view; B, male genital capsule, dorsal view; C, valve and subgenital plates, ventral view; D, connective and style, dorsal view; E, aedeagus, ventral view; F, style, connective and aedeagus, lateral view." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/182579/files/figure.png" pageId="5" pageNumber="6">
Fig. 
<number box="[771,786,490,516]" pageId="5" pageNumber="6" value="3.0">3</number>
</figureCitation>
B).
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="5.[151,1437,290,956]" box="[197,1143,530,556]" pageId="5" pageNumber="6">
Female genital capsule with apex acute, with dense short to long setae (
<figureCitation box="[1035,1106,530,556]" captionStart="FIGURE 4" captionStartId="17.[151,255,1787,1811]" captionTargetBox="[189,1383,231,1728]" captionTargetId="figure@17.[164,1418,194,1763]" captionTargetPageId="17" captionText="FIGURE 4. Cyrta horne i A, female genital capsule, lateral view; B, first valvula and detail of sculptures of first valvula; C, apex of female abdomen, ventral view; D, second valvula and detail of sculptures of second valvula; E, third valvula." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/182580/files/figure.png" pageId="5" pageNumber="6">
Fig. 
<number box="[1090,1106,530,556]" pageId="5" pageNumber="6" value="4.0">4</number>
</figureCitation>
A).
</paragraph>
