<subSubSection pageId="5" pageNumber="6" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="5.[151,1437,290,956]" pageId="5" pageNumber="6">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[197,318,690,716]" pageId="5" pageNumber="6">Remarks.</emphasis>
This species was erected as the 
<typeStatus box="[713,764,690,716]" pageId="5" pageNumber="6">type</typeStatus>
species of 
<taxonomicName box="[901,1004,690,715]" class="Insecta" family="Cicadellidae" genus="Placidus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="5" pageNumber="6" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[901,1004,690,715]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="6">Placidus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, but there has been some confusion regarding its identity (see Discussion below). In the present paper we take the identity of 
<taxonomicName box="[1214,1290,730,755]" class="Insecta" family="Cicadellidae" genus="Placidus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="5" pageNumber="6" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="hornei">
<emphasis box="[1214,1290,730,755]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="6">hornei</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(and that of genus 
<taxonomicName box="[227,329,770,795]" class="Insecta" family="Cicadellidae" genus="Placidus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="5" pageNumber="6" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[227,329,770,795]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="6">Placidus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
) from its unique 
<typeStatus box="[534,585,770,796]" pageId="5" pageNumber="6">type</typeStatus>
and recognize 
<taxonomicName box="[763,865,770,795]" class="Insecta" family="Cicadellidae" genus="Placidus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="5" pageNumber="6" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[763,865,770,795]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="6">Placidus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
as a junior synonym of 
<taxonomicName box="[1151,1218,770,795]" class="Insecta" family="Cicadellidae" genus="Cyrta" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="5" pageNumber="6" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[1151,1218,770,795]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="6">Cyrta</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. We also establish that the figures of 
<taxonomicName box="[366,472,810,835]" class="Insecta" family="Cicadellidae" genus="Placidus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="5" pageNumber="6" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="hornei">
<emphasis box="[366,472,810,835]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="6">P. hornei</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
by 
<bibRefCitation author="Evans" box="[515,673,810,836]" pageId="5" pageNumber="13" refString="Evans, J. W. (1971) Two new genus and species of Oriental Cicadellidae and remarks on the significance of the male genitalia in leafhopper classification (Homoptera: Cicadelloidea). Journal of Entomology, 40, 43 - 48." type="journal article" year="1971">
Evans (
<number box="[603,664,810,836]" pageId="5" pageNumber="6" value="1971.0">1971</number>
)
</bibRefCitation>
are of a different species which is similar to 
<taxonomicName authority="Wei &amp; Zhang. As Zhang &amp; Wei (2002)" authorityName="Wei &amp; Zhang. As Zhang &amp; Wei" authorityYear="2002" class="Insecta" family="Cicadellidae" genus="Placidus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="5" pageNumber="6" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="incurvatus">
<emphasis box="[1199,1352,810,835]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="6">P. incurvatus</emphasis>
Wei &amp; Zhang. As Zhang &amp; Wei (
<number box="[463,525,850,876]" pageId="5" pageNumber="6" value="2002.0">2002</number>
)
</taxonomicName>
figured only the aedeagus, style and connective of the 
<typeStatus box="[1194,1299,850,876]" pageId="5" pageNumber="6">holotype</typeStatus>
, and reproduced the figure of genital capsule by 
<bibRefCitation author="Evans" box="[595,754,890,916]" pageId="5" pageNumber="13" refString="Evans, J. W. (1971) Two new genus and species of Oriental Cicadellidae and remarks on the significance of the male genitalia in leafhopper classification (Homoptera: Cicadelloidea). Journal of Entomology, 40, 43 - 48." type="journal article" year="1971">
Evans (
<number box="[683,746,890,916]" pageId="5" pageNumber="6" value="1971.0">1971</number>
)
</bibRefCitation>
, we take the opportunity to figure the male genital capsule of the 
<typeStatus box="[226,329,930,956]" pageId="5" pageNumber="6">holotype</typeStatus>
for the first time in this paper (
<figureCitation box="[694,767,930,956]" captionStart="FIGURE 3" captionStartId="16.[151,255,1541,1565]" captionTargetBox="[202,1390,252,1497]" captionTargetId="figure@16.[163,1439,194,1517]" captionTargetPageId="16" captionText="FIGURE 3. Cyrta hornei, E-F are after Zhang &amp; Wei (2002). A, male genital capsule, lateral view; B, male genital capsule, dorsal view; C, valve and subgenital plates, ventral view; D, connective and style, dorsal view; E, aedeagus, ventral view; F, style, connective and aedeagus, lateral view." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/182579/files/figure.png" pageId="5" pageNumber="6">
Figs 
<number box="[754,767,930,956]" pageId="5" pageNumber="6" value="3.0">3</number>
</figureCitation>
A–C).
</paragraph>
